<br>
I believe there is OVERWHELMING evidence supporting the existence of God.  I also believe there is OVERWHELMING evidence supporting the facts of the New Testament.  But like most, I've shared my frustrations trying to verbalize what I know to be true.<br>
<br>
In my personal search to communicate this truth, I've come across a number of convincing resources.  If I were to recommend a few, I'd start with 2 incredible books.  They were both written by an aethiest who in his pursuit to discredit Christianity found Christ.  By reading his books and reflecting upon the Bible, I believe it takes more faith to NOT believe in God.<br>
<br>
The author of these books is Lee Strobel, and his books are &quot;The Case for Christ&quot; (ISBN: 0-310-20930-7) and &quot;The Case for Faith&quot; (ISBN: 0-310-23469-7).  <br>
<br>
The first of these 2 books challenges the Christian Faith with hard-hitting questions like: How reliable is the New Testament?  Does evidence exist for Jesus outside the Bible?  Is there any reason to believe the resurrection was an actual event?  <br>
<br>
His 2nd book addresses the most persistent emotional objections to belief -- the eight &quot;heart&quot; barriers to faith such as: If there's a loving God, why does this pain-wracked world groan under so much suffering and evil?  If the miracles of God contradict science, then how can any rational person believe they're true?  If God cares about the people he created, how could he consign so many of them to an eternity of torture in hell just because they didn't believe the right things about him?  If God is the ultimate overseer of the church, why has it been rife with hypocrisy and brutality throughout the ages?<br>
<br>
I believe Lee Strobel to be a credible author and legal investigator, having his Master of Studies in Law from Yale Law School and having been an award-winning legal editor for the Chicago Tribune.  Both books are intriguing, reading like a fascinating novel.  But it's not fiction. <br>
<br>
I am a Christian.  Like any of you who've taken the time to read this thread, I struggle to understand these very important questions.  I would be delighted to speak with any of you in private about this topic.  You can email me:<br>
<br>
christ_apologist@yahoo.com<br>
<br>
